# Python backend rules

- Use typed Python and explicit DTO/schema objects at API boundaries.
- Keep route handlers thin; put business logic in services and policies.
- Keep repository/storage interfaces separate from SQLite implementation details.
- Background jobs must persist state transitions and resume safely after restart.
- Ingest code must support per-report outcomes and idempotent retry behavior.
- Use the standard `logging` module and avoid ad hoc print debugging in production paths.
- Avoid hidden coupling between auth mode and domain authorization rules.
- Prefer descriptive names over abbreviations in policy and service modules.
